name: market for natural gas, burned in gas turbine | natural gas, burned in gas turbine | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/26806/documentation

This is the market for "natural gas, burned in gas turbine" [MJ of fuel input], in the Global geography.;This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;The activity "natural gas, burned in gas turbine" represents the use of a fossil fuel, primarily intended for energy supply throughout the transmission and distribution of natural gas. It is used as a gaseous fuel and is sourced from oil and gas production and evaporation of liquid natural gas. This exchange provides the service of burning 1 MJ of natural gas in a gas turbine. The services also includes (air) emissions, infrastructure and the production and provision of fuel. 1 MJ fuel input equals 0.0278 m3 of natural gas.

This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce "natural gas, burned in gas turbine", within the geography of Global.

This activity ends with the supply of natural gas, burned in gas turbine", to the consumers of this product. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.
